cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for computer vision problems such as image classification, object detection, and image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the proposed architecture is end-to-end trainable and applicable to a wide range of computer vision problems, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Residual Networks and the focus on improving computational efficiency suggest that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of computation time maps on the visual saliency dataset suggests that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
